data.content:
Từ điển Anh - Việt
◘['kuki]
*danh từ
 ■(Ê-cốt) bánh bao
 ■(từ Mỹ,nghĩa Mỹ) bánh dẹt nhỏ, bánh quy

Anh - Anh
cookie
■ noun (plural cookies)
1》 N. Amer. a sweet biscuit.
2》 informal a person of a specified kind: she's a tough cookie.
3》 Scottish a plain bun.
4》 Computing a packet of data sent by an Internet server to a browser and used to identify the user or track their access to the server.
Phrases
that's the way the cookie crumblesinformal, chiefly N. Amer. that's the situation, and it must be accepted, however undesirable.
Origin
C18: from Du. koekje 'little cake', dimin. of koek.

Kết hợp từ & Cấu trúc câu
cookie
n.
1) (AE) a homemade; sandwich cookie
2) a fortune cookie
